                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d743">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">881.00/1810: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at Tangier</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">White</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-24T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 24, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>93. My telegram to the Department 89, December 18, 4 p.m. My British colleague is
                    proceeding to Madrid today to help draft a project of a <hi rend="italic">modus
                        vivendi</hi> with the Spanish Government for British interests in
                    Tangier.</p>
                <p>The Legation’s telegram No. 92, December 21, 9 p.m.,<note n="35"
                        xml:id="d743fn35">Not printed.</note> please disregard the final
                    paragraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
